File: platform/mcp-server/src/index.ts:197

Current code:
  log.info(`MCP server listening on http://localhost:${actualPort}`);

Fix: Import version from './version.js' and include it in the log line:
  import { version } from './version.js';
  log.info(`MCP server v${version} listening on http://localhost:${actualPort}`);

The version module already exists at platform/mcp-server/src/version.ts and is already imported by mcp-setup.ts and health endpoint code. Just add the import to index.ts.

Pattern reference: platform/mcp-server/src/mcp-setup.ts uses `import { version } from './version.js';`

File: platform/create-plugin/src/index.ts

Current code (line 7-8):
  const program = new Command('create-opentabs-plugin')
    .description('Scaffold a new OpenTabs plugin project')

Fix: Read version from package.json and add .version() call. Follow the exact same pattern used in platform/cli/src/cli.ts lines 19-23:

  import { dirname, join } from 'node:path';
  import { fileURLToPath } from 'node:url';

  const cliDir = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));
  const pkgJson = JSON.parse(await Bun.file(join(cliDir, '..', 'package.json')).text()) as { version: string };

  const program = new Command('create-opentabs-plugin')
    .version(pkgJson.version, '-V, --version')
    .description('Scaffold a new OpenTabs plugin project')

The imports for dirname, join, fileURLToPath are not yet in the file — add them.

Pattern reference: platform/cli/src/cli.ts:19-23 does exactly this.
